metadata.title: How to customize my store? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: If you want to change it manually, let's see how you can change it as per your requirement. Primary Color - This color sets the overall theme of your store. Changing this will change the color of buttons and the left side category selector. For example, here we changed the primary color to a new color. This is how it will be shown in the store. Secondary Color - This is the secondary color scheme of your store. This will not change the overall look and feel of the store, but some part of it. For example, we have changed the secondary color to a new color. This is how it will be shown in the store.Menu Bar Color - This will change the menu bar's color which is displayed on the top if you have enabled it on your store. For example, we have changed the menu bar color to a new color. This is how it will be shown in the store.Things you can customize in Favicon:Once you click on Favicon, you can see an option to change it. A favicon, also known as a website icon or URL icon is a file containing one or more small icons, associated with a particular website or web page. You can change it to show your brand's short logo or any other image.  By default, Dukaan's logo is shown as a Favicon if left unchanged. To change the Favicon, click on the Change Image button and upload the desired image. For example, here I have changed the Favicon to a new icon. This is how it will be shown on your website. Now it's time for you to use Customize and design your store the way you want.Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.title: How to add policies to my store? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to add policies to my store? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsStore ProfileHow to add policies to my store?How to add policies to my store?Learn how to add return, refund and terms & conditions policies to your storeNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoNow you can add Return, Refund, Terms & Conditions policies to your Dukaan store with just a few clicks. To add them, go to Account and click on Policies.  Here you can see all three policies templates. We suggest you review the content of the policy and make changes as per your store before applying them. Once you've made changes to the policies, click on Add as store page button. Now, to display these policies on your store, click on Appearance and choose Menus.   Under the Pages section, click on the Policy Name checkbox to select and then click on Add to Menu button.  Click on the Save Menu button to make changes. Once done, select policies will be shown on your store.Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.title: How to bulk add products? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: Variant Display Price: Enter the MRP of the product.Variant weight unit: Choose the appropriate weight unit for the product from the drop-down menu.Product GST/Tax Value ( Percentage): Add the tax percentage you will be charging for the product.EAN/HSN Code: Enter the EAN/HSN code of the product.SEO title: Enter an SEO-optimized meta title for your product.SEO description: Enter an SEO-optimized meta description for your product.Note Entering data in the SEO categories will enable the SEO plugin and add the values accordinglyOnce you have all the details, save the file. metadata.title: How to Auto Accept Orders? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to Auto Accept Orders? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsStore ProfileHow to Auto Accept Orders?How to Auto Accept Orders?Learn how to turn on Auto-accept orders functionality on your Dukaan storeNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoPresently, when an order is received on your Dukaan store, it goes to the 'Pending' stage and you need to manually accept the order. With the auto-accept order preference, you can choose to auto-accept certain types of orders. These orders will automatically move to the 'Accepted' stage. To use this functionality, click on the dropdown in the top right corner. Now, click on Store Settings. Select Preferences from the panel on the left. By default, the functionality of the Auto-accept orders is set to 'Never'. Click on it to change it.The following dialogue box opens: You can choose to auto-accept:COD orders onlyPrepaid orders onlyAll (COD + Prepaid) ordersNeverSelect the type of orders you would like to auto-accept and click on Save changes.Read MoreHow to use Preferences section on Web?How to use Advance Catalogue?How to take bulk actions on orders?Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.title: How to use the WooCommerce Importer? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to use the WooCommerce Importer? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsPluginsHow to use the WooCommerce Importer?How to use the WooCommerce Importer?Learn how to use the WooCommerce importer and shift to DukaanWritten by Jyotbir Lamba Updated over a week agoUse the WooCommerce importer to migrate your products seamlessly to Dukaan. The in house plugin allows you to migrate an existing WooCommerce store to Dukaan.  The WooCommerce importer saves you from the hassle of manually adding details of your products one-by-one and completes the entire process quickly. Here, you will need to share the website link, consumer key and the consumer secret from the WooCommerce dashboard. (Note: The plugin will import a maximum of 500 products)How to install the WooCommerce importer pluginClick on install plugin and head over to the plugin Settings. Here you will need to enter the Store link, Consumer key, Consumer Secret from your WooCommerce dashboard.  How to obtain your consumer key and consumer secret from WooCommerce Head over to your WooCommerce dashboardSelect Advanced from the Settings menu and click on Rest API buttonClick on the Add key buttonAdd Description, select the Read/Write permission for the key and click Generate API keyCopy the "Consumer key" and "Consumer secret" provided and paste them on your Dukaan plugin settings pageAfter entering the required details, click on ImportUpon clicking on Import, all the products (Max 500 products) will be imported into your Dukaan storeYou will be able to edit the product details in the Product section of your Dukaan dashboard. Video Tutorial:Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.title: How to use the Mailmunch plugin? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to use the Mailmunch plugin? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsPluginsHow to use the Mailmunch plugin?How to use the Mailmunch plugin?Learn how to grow your audience and boost sales with the Mailmunch pluginNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoMailMunch is the complete lead generation toolkit for your Dukaan store. It makes it easier to collect more leads and keep them engaged with your brand.  Choose from popovers, covers, scroll boxes, top bars, embedded forms, and more to create the perfect form for every campaign. Here’s how you can start using the Mailmunch plugin:Create your account on MailMunch and add your siteClick on your website name on the MailMunch dashboardGo to the Site Settings on the left sidebar  Click on Get Site Code on the top right corner of the page.  Copy the mailmunch-site-id from the code snippet. Please note that the site ID would be a number (for example: 992423)  Install the MailMunch plugin from Dukaan Dashboard and paste the ID in the settings page  Click Update to finish installing the pluginDid this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.title: How to add FSSAI license number to your store? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to add FSSAI license number to your store? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsStore ProfileHow to add FSSAI license number to your store?How to add FSSAI license number to your store?NWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoNote: This is applicable only to users in India. Every food business operator involved in the manufacturing, processing, storage distribution, and sale of food products must compulsorily obtain FSSAI Registration or License. It is a 14-digit registration or a license number. Now you can add the FSSAI License number to your Dukaan Store from the app and web. To add your FSSAI number, your business should be in the following categories:Kirana Store, FMCG, GroceryRestaurants & HotelsFruits & VegetablesFresh Chicken, Fish & MeatTo add the FSSAI number, go to My Account and then click Edit Business Details. Here, you'll see a new field FSSAI Number. Enter your business's FSSAI License mber here and click on Save to finish.  To update the FSSAI number from the app, go to Account and click on Edit business details. Now update the number in the FSSAI number field.   Once updated, all new orders receipts will have this FSSAI number mentioned for reference.    Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

In order to create an additional store, click on your store name at the top of your Dukaan dashboard. You will see the subtext Switch store.  The following dialogue box opens You will then see the number of stores you have created and the stores you can create. For example, in the above screenshot, we have created 1 store and can create up to 10 stores. Now, in order to create a new store, click on or create a new store You will then be directed to the sign up screen for the new store as below. As you can see in the below image, after setting up your new store, the number of stores has been increased to 2 from 1 earlier. You can choose which store to log in from here by clicking on it. In case you wish to see your store wise plan limits, you can head to the subscription settings in your Account settings You will be able to see your plan limits and features here.Read moreHow to use the Staff Account feature?How to link your third-party custom domain on Dukaan?How can I add my custom domain name from Dukaan?Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom
